# La Nueva Recoleta — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
Landing page for "La Nueva Recoleta", a bakery & café in Buenos Aires.
Stack: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4 + Framer Motion.

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Always use TypeScript with strict mode. No `any` types — use `unknown` if the type is truly dynamic.
- Prefer `interface` for component props, `type` for unions and utility types.
- Export types from `src/types/index.ts`.
- Use proper null handling with optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`).

### React
- Functional components only. No class components.
- Name components in PascalCase, files match the component name.
- Keep components small and focused. Extract logic into custom hooks under `src/hooks/`.
- Use `React.RefObject<HTMLElement>` when typing refs. Never cast as `any`.
- Prefer named exports for components.

### Tailwind CSS v4
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly. No `@apply` unless strictly needed for global base styles.
- Brand colors defined in `src/index.css` under `@theme`. Use them as: `bg-brand-burgundy`, `text-brand-cream`, etc.
- Brand fonts: `font-[Playfair_Display]`, `font-[Dancing_Script]`, `font-[Inter]`.
- Mobile-first: start with base (mobile) styles, then add `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints.
- Use `transition-all duration-300` as the default transition. Prefer smooth, non-jarring values.

### Framer Motion
- Use `motion.div`, `motion.section`, etc. for animated elements.
- For scroll-triggered animations, prefer `whileInView` with `viewport={{ once: true, margin: '-80px' }}`.
- Use `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit animations.
- Use the `useInView` custom hook for imperative scroll detection.
- Keep animations subtle: `y: [0, 20]`, opacity fades, slight scale changes. No excessive movement.

### File Structure
```
src/
  components/
    layout/     # Navbar, Footer
    sections/   # Hero, About, Menu, Reviews, Location
    ui/         # Reusable small components (StarRating, Button, etc.)
  hooks/        # Custom React hooks
  types/        # TypeScript interfaces and types
  data/         # Mock data and constants
  assets/
    images/     # Static images
    video/      # Hero video
```

## Design Tokens (Brand)
- Primary: `#7B1C1C` (burgundy)
- Primary Dark: `#5A1010`
- Primary Light: `#9B2D2D`
- Cream: `#FAF6F0`
- Brown: `#3D1F0D`
- Gold: `#C9973A`
- Background: `#1A1008` (charcoal-brown)

## Naming Conventions
- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Hook files: `useCamelCase.ts`
- Utility files: `camelCase.ts`
- CSS classes: Tailwind only, no custom class names unless necessary

## Performance
- Lazy load images with `loading="lazy"` attribute.
- Use `next/image` equivalent pattern: always provide `width`, `height`, and `alt`.
- Videos must have `autoPlay muted loop playsInline` and a `poster` fallback.
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders: memoize with `useMemo`/`useCallback` only when profiling shows benefit.

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `aria-describedby`).
- Use semantic HTML: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`.
- Buttons must have visible focus states.
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA minimum.

## API Integration (Fudo — coming soon)
- API service functions go in `src/services/fudoApi.ts`.
- Use React Query (TanStack Query) for data fetching when implemented.
- Types for API responses go in `src/types/fudo.ts`.
- Keep mock data in `src/data/mockData.ts` as fallback.

## Git
- Commit messages in imperative mood, in Spanish or English.
- Branch naming: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`.
- No direct commits to `main`.
